node.text:
The second most asked question I get is - how do you walk in heels all day?
So what better way to start - the back to my original profile photo - than with a video of me walking (and running) in heels starting with a 100mm heel on to the 120mm and finishing with #HotChick 130mm (as seen in my profile photo). Please remember though, I might be in heels a lot but I, almost always, bring a pair of flats with me. In my car, bag if the size allows or sometimes I’ll just carry them in an extra shopping bag. BUT I did start wearing flats more and more though. 
When I’m in new shoes, the easiest way for me to break them in, is to put lotion on my feet before slipping them on. I’ll bring the lotion with me and keep re-applying throughout the day/night. That has, always, saved me from getting blisters. 
How did I learn how to walk in heels? I started with lower heelheights and gradually went higher. I did however walk around, at home, in them until I knew I didn’t look like a penguin about to slip before heading out that firsbt time. 
Because remember ladies (and boys!) it’s sexier to walk in flats than to strut around looking like that penguin...

node.text:
Jesse.

Words can’t express the loss of our deeply beloved little boy. Our Jesse.
After 10.5 years of devotion, happiness, travels, snuggles and true love he passed away, in my arms, at the comfort of our home on July 31 at 5.05pm.

Forever missed. Forever loved.
Forever thankful for the years we got to walk this earth together.

I’ll see you in heaven little man.
